member.summary: Gets the default configuration.

member.summary: Gets or sets value indicating whether visitor engagement calculation is enabled.

member.summary: Gets or sets the target time frame (in days).

member.name: P:Dynamicweb.Analytics.Configuration.VisitorEngagementConfiguration.ClickDepth
member.summary: Gets or sets the "Click depth" rule.
member.remarks: The meaning of this rule is how many points does the visitor get if the number of pages visits is greater or equal to the given value.

member.name: P:Dynamicweb.Analytics.Configuration.VisitorEngagementConfiguration.Loyalty
member.summary: Gets or sets the "Loyalty" rule.
member.remarks: The meaning of this rule is how many points does the visitor get if the number of subsequent visits is greater or equal to the given value.

member.name: P:Dynamicweb.Analytics.Configuration.VisitorEngagementConfiguration.Recency
member.summary: Gets or sets the "Recency" rule.
member.remarks: The meaning of this rule is how many points does the visitor get if the last visit date falls within the given frame (number of days).

member.name: P:Dynamicweb.Analytics.Configuration.VisitorEngagementConfiguration.BrandedSearch
member.summary: Gets or sets the "Branded search" rule.
member.remarks: The meaning of this rule is how many points does the visitor get if the referrer is the search engine and the search phrase contains any of the given keywords.

member.name: P:Dynamicweb.Analytics.Configuration.VisitorEngagementConfiguration.Interactions
member.summary: Gets or sets the list of "Interaction" rules.
member.remarks: The meaning of this rule is how many points does the visitor get for performing a specific interaction on a website (e.g. submit a form, view the product, etc.).

member.name: P:Dynamicweb.Analytics.Leads.VisitorEngagementSettings.BrandedSearch
member.summary: Gets or sets the "Branded search" rule.
member.remarks: The meaning of this rule is how many points does the visitor get if the referrer is the search engine and the search phrase contains any of the given keywords.

member.name: P:Dynamicweb.Analytics.Leads.VisitorEngagementSettings.Interactions
member.summary: Gets or sets the list of "Interaction" rules.

member.name: T:Dynamicweb.Analytics.ParagraphSegmentSelection
member.summary: A table with segments selections(which are basically users smart searches). if a user belongs to at least one segment that has the "stop" icon, the paragraph is not rendered for this user. When a paragraph is set to "show", the only options for each segment is "hide" or "ignore". Similarly, if it is set to "hide", that is, the red "stop" icon, it is only shown to users that belong to at least one segment that has the green checkmark. When a paragraph is set to "hide", the only options for each segment are "show" and "ignore".
